title: Statement by the Press Secretary on the President's Trip to France | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
November 01, 2011

 



Statement by the Press Secretary on the President's Trip to France




Yesterday at midnight, NATOâ€™s Operation Unified Protector concluded after seven months of a successful effort to protect the Libyan people and support them as they won their freedom. Following the G-20 Summit, on November 4 the President and President Sarkozy of France will participate in a ceremony in Cannes to honor the alliance between the United States and France. At this ceremony, the two Presidents will meet with American and French service members who served together in Operation Unified Protector.
